        <div class="ts-faq__content ts-fs-6">
          <ol class="ts-faq-item">
            <li>
              <span class="fw-700">
                What type of designer do I need?
              </span>
              <p>
                Typically, it’s difficult to find a designer who is good at the entire spectrum of
                design, ranging from user research, interaction design, visual design, branding,
                etc. So it depends on the challenges that you’re currently trying to solve. For
                example, if your team has strong user research capabilities, you could choose a
                designer who is stronger with interaction design or visual design.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="fw-700">
                How do I evaluate design candidates?
              </span>
              <p>
                It takes an experienced designer to evaluate other designers. It’s also important
                that you person evaluating the designer can tell the difference between someone who
                is used to design in big companies versus startups. Experience in either comes with
                advantages and challenges. It doesn’t mean that you should only hire candidates with
                startup experience. With either, there might be some mental shifts that need to
                happen for the designer to be able to do their best work.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="fw-700">
                How do I get my team, that has never worked with a great designer, to appreciate Design?
              </span>
              <p>
                It’s wonderful that you understand the importance of Design. If your company is
                still in its early stages and doesn’t yet have a designer, finding the right first
                hire is crucial. Or finding an experienced design leader who you can partner with in
                your effort. Appreciation comes from working with a competent designer who will need
                your help to champion their efforts. 
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="fw-700">
                How can designers at startups benefit from coaching?
              </span>
              <p>
                Startups, especially early-stage ones, have unique qualities that might be foreign
                to designers who have never worked in such an environment before. If the company
                does not have strong design leadership, the designer’s growth could stagnate. In
                order to do their best work and meet the needs of a growing startup, having a mentor
                who understand the ins and outs of startup environment and needs will help
                tremendously.
              </p>
            </li>
